      <acqinfo id="aspace_fc47b4dd41879b6e626306a58de0879a">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The Collection of Book Illustrations was housed in the former Arts of the Book Collection until its transfer to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library in 2008.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_c760397441933b6597451382afc02ba0">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <userestrict id="aspace_fdb0b087e9481f47efe725a817d5a9c8">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.</p>  
      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_2f5ec07dba6fa1f4f90e74b7a4806314">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Collection of Book Illustrations, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_43991f92bc6765f10dd3462026fba96e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection comprises illustrations salvaged from damaged bound volumes. Thus, many plates are lacking for each publication.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_78516fc6e44a2c11145e2e36789bd0c1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into three series: I. English. II. French. III. German.</p>
         <p>The materials are arranged by language (of publication or publisher). If known, the publication is identified. Otherwise, a description of the subject matter identifies the materials.</p>  
      </arrangement>
